WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.950 --> 00:00:06.180
- The Rainbow Mountain is one

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:09.000
of Peru's most iconic tourism sites.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:10.470
- Rainbow Mountain, all to yourself.

00:00:10.470 --> 00:00:12.750
- It is made for going viral.

00:00:12.750 --> 00:00:15.255
- It's beautiful though. We did see it.

00:00:15.255 --> 00:00:17.290
- Suddenly because of global tourism,

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:21.450
it became a symbol of violence.

00:00:23.610 --> 00:00:25.055
Now somebody has been killed.

00:01:09.330 --> 00:01:10.890
Money can do a lot of good.

00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.515
It can really transform people's lives,

00:01:13.515 --> 00:01:14.815
but it can also hurt them.

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:10.620
The Rainbow Mountain sits in
the southern Peruvian Andes,

00:02:10.620 --> 00:02:12.450
the most impoverished part of the country.

00:02:14.280 --> 00:02:17.400
One thing you realize when
you travel to the Andes

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:19.470
is that usually the center of power

00:02:19.470 --> 00:02:21.450
of any indigenous community
will be the lowest

00:02:21.450 --> 00:02:23.580
part of that mountain.

00:02:23.580 --> 00:02:26.370
The higher you go, the
fewer things will grow

00:02:26.370 --> 00:02:27.810
and the fewer opportunities you'll have.

00:06:27.426 --> 00:06:29.375
- Rainbow Mountain.

00:06:29.375 --> 00:06:32.913
- Maybe it was worth the hike. I think so.

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:54.980
- Peru is a mining nation.

00:06:54.980 --> 00:06:57.740
Mining companies scout the Andes

00:06:57.740 --> 00:06:59.840
because they're so rich in minerals.

00:06:59.840 --> 00:07:03.140
And just as the Rainbow
Mountain is becoming known

00:07:03.140 --> 00:07:05.030
to the world for the first time,

00:07:05.030 --> 00:07:07.100
mining companies also get interested

00:07:07.100 --> 00:07:09.260
and they buy mineral rights
to the area under it.

00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:50.810
One of the most common struggles

00:07:50.810 --> 00:07:53.330
with mining companies
is their relationship

00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:54.560
with indigenous communities.

00:08:02.180 --> 00:08:06.685
Many indigenous Peruvians
have been killed in protests

00:08:06.685 --> 00:08:10.340
against mining, but the State
has always had a clear line.

00:08:10.340 --> 00:08:12.320
If there are minerals under it,

00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:13.795
we should try to extract them.

00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:40.310
The Rainbow Mountain
got so big so quickly,

00:08:40.310 --> 00:08:43.160
that the president himself
got involved to ensure

00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:45.350
that the mountain would be preserved

00:08:45.350 --> 00:08:48.110
and that it would not be
given to mining companies.

00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:53.240
Saving a mountain from mining
in Peru is no small feat.

00:08:53.240 --> 00:08:56.310
So really, when the mineral
rights were revoked,

00:08:56.310 --> 00:09:00.870
people thought that tourism
would be this blessing for

00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:01.885
the local community.

00:10:13.175 --> 00:10:17.370
Because of Flavio's advocacy
for Rainbow Mountain,

00:10:17.370 --> 00:10:20.340
he becomes president of the community

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:22.260
and the State is playing catch up.

00:10:22.260 --> 00:10:24.450
And so there's a deal
reach between the community

00:10:24.450 --> 00:10:26.100
and the local municipality

00:10:26.100 --> 00:10:28.530
to split the revenue
from Rainbow Mountain.

00:10:28.530 --> 00:10:31.080
And things appear to be in peace.

00:10:31.080 --> 00:10:35.010
But the reality is they
are vying for power,

00:10:35.010 --> 00:10:37.290
vying for control of ticket revenues.

00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:39.090
There is no state support.

00:10:39.090 --> 00:10:42.673
No programs meant to ensure
transparency.

00:10:42.673 --> 00:10:43.506
There is nothing.

00:10:43.506 --> 00:10:46.050
It is a situation where
a lot can go wrong,

00:10:46.050 --> 00:10:48.050
and in this case it did.

00:11:27.263 --> 00:11:29.670
While Flavio is a visionary at first,

00:11:29.670 --> 00:11:31.836
he soon runs into obstacles
carrying out

00:11:31.836 --> 00:11:34.919
this revenue split deal
with the municipality.

00:11:37.830 --> 00:11:40.590
The community is suddenly
missing money,

00:11:40.590 --> 00:11:44.730
and because of this, Flavio
finds himself in tension

00:11:44.730 --> 00:11:46.710
with another community leader.

00:11:46.710 --> 00:11:48.251
Cecilio Quispe Noa.

00:12:06.070 --> 00:12:08.470
There are really two main
groups to this story.

00:12:08.470 --> 00:12:10.603
On the one hand, you have
Chillihuani,

00:12:10.603 --> 00:12:12.803
the normal center of
power of this community.

00:12:12.803 --> 00:12:15.612
And on the other you have Llacto.

00:12:17.860 --> 00:12:20.980
Cecilio becomes president
of the Chillihuani community

00:12:20.980 --> 00:12:23.800
and he takes control of the ticket revenue

00:12:23.800 --> 00:12:26.825
and he neglects the Llacto sector

00:12:26.825 --> 00:12:28.992
and that brews resentment.

00:14:51.110 --> 00:14:53.480
- Part of what makes
Rainbow Mountain a recipe

00:14:53.480 --> 00:14:54.860
for disaster

00:14:54.860 --> 00:14:57.500
is that there is no state
presence administering it.

00:14:57.500 --> 00:14:59.390
And so these tensions about the handling

00:14:59.390 --> 00:15:02.150
of the money continue to escalate,

00:15:02.150 --> 00:15:03.920
and the very highest levels

00:15:03.920 --> 00:15:07.520
of Peru's government
suddenly gets involved.

00:15:07.520 --> 00:15:09.260
There is one thing that needs to be done.

00:15:09.260 --> 00:15:13.580
The Rainbow Mountain
route needs to be shut down.

00:15:36.290 --> 00:15:39.410
The communities meet on August 8th,

00:15:39.410 --> 00:15:41.300
but at this point, tensions are sky high.

00:16:04.820 --> 00:16:07.905
Cecilio attends this round table meeting

00:16:07.905 --> 00:16:10.910
and he takes a very drastic position.

00:16:31.850 --> 00:16:35.025
Cecilio says, we are
an indigenous community

00:16:35.025 --> 00:16:39.535
and the State should not be
in any position to regulate,

00:16:39.535 --> 00:16:41.527
oversee, or tax us.

00:16:45.666 --> 00:16:47.083
And then he walks out

00:21:35.620 --> 00:21:37.390
What Edit had been warning,

00:21:37.390 --> 00:21:40.030
that there could be a fatal confrontation,

00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:42.010
it is finally taking place.

00:21:42.010 --> 00:21:44.980
She calls the police desperately.

00:21:44.980 --> 00:21:46.813
Eventually, one police car

00:21:46.813 --> 00:21:49.510
goes up to the town of Chillihuani

00:21:49.510 --> 00:21:51.820
where they're met with the same mob

00:21:51.820 --> 00:21:54.028
who throws stones at the
police car.

00:21:55.095 --> 00:21:57.519
Feeling outnumbered they turned around.

00:22:00.061 --> 00:22:01.769
There's absolute chaos.

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:06.748
But there's also a sense
of paralysis,

00:22:06.748 --> 00:22:08.831
a sense of powerlessness.

00:22:08.831 --> 00:22:10.390
A decision has been made,

00:22:10.390 --> 00:22:12.850
and the decision is to wait until dawn

00:22:12.850 --> 00:22:14.865
to do anything about this aggression.

00:25:31.225 --> 00:25:32.930
The police report suggests that up

00:25:32.930 --> 00:25:35.840
to 80 people made up this mob

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:37.640
that attacked and killed Flavio.

00:25:37.640 --> 00:25:39.530
His body is found lying flat,

00:25:39.530 --> 00:25:42.080
and he has bled from his skull.

00:25:42.080 --> 00:25:45.470
He had died from blunt
trauma that was in line

00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.840
with having been stoned to death.

00:25:55.220 --> 00:25:56.540
These are neighbors.

00:25:56.540 --> 00:25:58.098
These are people who have
lived together

00:25:58.098 --> 00:25:59.673
their entire lifetimes,

00:25:59.673 --> 00:26:02.398
and now the main witnesses are

00:26:02.398 --> 00:26:04.730
Filomeno and his wife.

00:26:04.730 --> 00:26:07.063
And they start naming names.

00:37:26.385 --> 00:37:29.850
- One important tradition
in Andean communities is

00:37:29.850 --> 00:37:32.220
to participate in local festivals.

00:37:35.130 --> 00:37:37.305
After Flavio's killing
the Llacto community

00:37:37.305 --> 00:37:38.705
decides they want to honor him

00:37:38.705 --> 00:37:40.420
and do a reinterpretation

00:37:40.420 --> 00:37:42.970
of his death in the form of a dance.

00:38:00.780 --> 00:38:02.820
They're still hurting.

00:38:02.820 --> 00:38:06.210
They're not able to freely
talk about what has happened

00:38:06.210 --> 00:38:08.760
because they're in
conflict with one another.

00:38:08.760 --> 00:38:13.290
And this dance, in a way, is
the only way for some people

00:38:13.290 --> 00:38:16.620
to show what in their view has happened,

00:38:16.620 --> 00:38:18.480
what the tragedy really looked like.

00:40:10.775 --> 00:40:14.170
Since Flavio's killing, around 20 members

00:40:14.170 --> 00:40:15.850
of the Chillihuani
community have been sent

00:40:15.850 --> 00:40:18.220
to pre-trial detention in Peru.

00:40:18.220 --> 00:40:20.770
Pre-trial detention can last years,

00:40:20.770 --> 00:40:23.710
and it is possible that we
will just simply never know

00:40:23.710 --> 00:40:24.790
who killed Flavio.

00:40:29.830 --> 00:40:34.030
The realization is one of hopelessness.

00:40:34.030 --> 00:40:36.340
How could this have happened?

00:40:36.340 --> 00:40:40.570
How could a community have
gotten into such a situation

00:40:40.570 --> 00:40:42.940
where they ended up killing each other?

00:40:42.940 --> 00:40:45.100
How could money do something like that?

